39 or self-insured employer receives written notice of such claims. A worker who fails to comply with
40 the communication requirements of subsection (6) of this section or ORS 656.267 may not allege at
41 any hearing or other proceeding on the claim a de facto denial of a condition based on information
42 in the notice of acceptance from the insurer or self-insured employer.
43 (b) Once a worker’s claim has been accepted, the insurer or self-insured employer must issue a
44 written denial to the worker when the accepted injury is no longer the major contributing cause
45 of the worker’s combined condition before the claim may be closed.
